</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[201,1313,1660,1684]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,973,1756]" box="[201,1313,1660,1684]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,336,1660,1684]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived by combining two words Sun + 
<taxonomicName box="[1026,1111,1660,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agallia</taxonomicName>
, gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,973,1756]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1696,1720]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
This brachypterous genus can be easily distinguished from all other Old World agalliine genera by the presence of a hooklike ventral process of the male pygofer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
